{
  "texts": [
    "When a device is jailbroken, it allows users to gain more control and access to the file system and core functions of the device [51].",
    "Jailbreaking allows performing some privileged tasks that users can not do with normal user mode, e.g., installing unapproved apps, unlocking due to country code, and accessing the file manipulation system [179].",
    "There are some potential risks to jailbreak the devices like losing functionality, security risks, and bricking [174].",
    "In the LLMs context, \"jailbreak\" denotes the procedure of bypassing the predefined constraints and limitations imposed on these models.",
    "According to Liu et al., [147], a Jailbreaking prompt is defined as a general template used to bypass restrictions."
  ]
}